headline: Starbucks union rejects company's recent offer of at least 2% annual pay raise
summary: "Starbucks' current offer is insufficient to finalize a deal," the workers union said.  Starbucks said in a statement that the union presented an incomplete framework for single-store contracts to their delegates to vote on, adding that its actions were causing a delay in reaching a mutual agreement.  The parties had been advancing contract negotiations in recent weeks after agreeing to bring in a mediator to help resume stalled negotiations in February.
